Taps don't fire for terminal invocations (event at end of pipeline)

When an event is the LAST thing in a flow (no destination), tap lookups
don't happen. The tap transformer only inserts taps at continuation
boundaries where there's a transition FROM source TO destination.

To fix: tap transformer needs to also check for taps on terminal
invocations where destination is null/terminal.

Related: The `-> *` pattern should probably match "to any destination
INCLUDING terminal" not just "to any concrete destination event".
